                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the north wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Achalēśvara shrine in the southeast corner of the second <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> in the Tyāgarājasvāmin temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Vīra-Bhūpati-Uḍaiyar. 1429 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This epigraph is dated in the reign of Mahāmaṇḍalīśvaran Śrī Vīra-Bhūpati-Uḍaiyar. The date given Kīlaka, Māśi 28, may correspond to 1429 A.D., February 22.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This seems to record a royal decree for the merchants (<hi rend="italic">vāṇikar</hi>).</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
